    <h1>Tutorial 7. Assembling the Front of the Lining.</h1>
    <p><strong>I start assembling the dress by joining the intermediate front pieces with the side front pieces</strong> or, simply put, sewing down the intermediate princess seams.</p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image002.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p><strong>I align the pieces following the control points transferred on the fabric.</strong></p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image004.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image006.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p><strong>And I secure them with pins and join them by machine.&nbsp; </strong></p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image008.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image010.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p><strong>I trim the ends of the seam allowance of the intermediate princess seam at an angle, open them, and topstitch them. </strong></p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image012.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image014.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image016.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image018.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image020.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image022.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p><strong>The other pair of pieces is sewn together just the same way. I topstitch the seam allowance of the intermediate princess seam just like I did before. </strong></p>
    <p><strong><br>
    <img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image024.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
    <p><strong><br>
    <img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image026.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
    <p><strong><br>
    <img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image028.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
    <p><strong><br>
    <img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image030.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
    <p><strong><br>
    <img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image032.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
    <p><strong>And now I will sew the bust princess seams, i.e. join the central front piece with the already joined intermediate and side front pieces.</strong></p>
    <p><strong>I align the control points to make sure the pieces will be joined correctly.</strong> There were basically no changes in the bust princess seams so the control points stayed the same as on the initial pattern. I pin the pieces together in the corresponding points.</p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image034.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image036.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p><strong>I notch the curved edge of the central front piece to straighten the joining seam. </strong>&nbsp;The notches are about 1cm deep.</p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image038.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p><strong>Next, I connect the point where the bust princess seam meets the intermediate princess seam with the point marked on the central piece, align the edges of the pieces, and continue notching the seam allowance of the joining seam.&nbsp; </strong></p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image040.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image042.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image044.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image046.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p><strong>I use a generous amount of pins to secure the pieces together.</strong></p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image048.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p><strong>I sew the pieces together by machine. </strong></p>
    <p><strong><br>
    <img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image050.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
    <p><strong><br>
    <img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image052.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
    <p><strong><br>
    <img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image054.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
    <p><strong><br>
    <img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image056.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
    <p><strong><br>
    <img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image058.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
    <p><strong>And I trim the corners of the seam allowance. </strong></p>
    <p><strong><br>
    <img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image060.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
    <p><strong>The bust princess seam looks very neat.</strong></p>
    <p><strong><br>
    <img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image062.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
    <p><strong>I will press open the seam allowance of the bust princess seam and press the seam allowances of other front princess seams flat toward the central front piece. For this purpose, I notch the seam allowance of the bottom border of the cup. </strong></p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image064.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p><strong>Now that the bust princess seam is sewn, the under-bust area is quite obviously asking for a tiny dart. </strong>Such things won't come as a surprise if you sew a mock-up first.</p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image066.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p><strong>I will form this dart now before I have sewn the other princess seam. </strong>I fold the central piece along the batiste leaving the stiff iron-on fabric at the top of the cup.</p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image068.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p><strong>I will sew a small dart from one corner of the batiste to the opposite corner. It is no deeper than 0.5cm. </strong></p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image070.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image072.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image074.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p><strong>I open and topstitch the seam allowance of the bust princess seam on the cup. </strong></p>
    <p><strong><br>
    <img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image076.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
    <p><strong><br>
    <img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image078.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
    <p><strong><br>
    <img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image080.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
    <p><strong>And I topstitch it flat onto the central front piece in the area from the end of the cup down to the bottom.</strong></p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image082.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image084.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image086.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p>If you are not very experience in sewing and don't feel like you can topstitch princess seams neatly without pressing them first, then simply press them using a good steam iron.</p>
    <p><strong>I trim the seam allowance of the princess seam on the cup. </strong></p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image088.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image090.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p><strong>Here is what the bust and intermediate front princess seams look like from the face and from the inside:</strong></p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image092.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image094.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p><strong>I sew the other bust princess seam forming a dart under the bust. </strong>The algorithm is the same as before.</p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image096.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image098.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image100.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image102.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image104.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image106.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image108.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image110.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image112.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image114.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image116.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image118.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p><strong>And now I will press the princess seams to make them flat and even.</strong> I use a cup pressing mould for pressing the princess seams on the cups and press all other pieces on a flat surface.&nbsp; The pieces might stretch out when you are joining them. If I notice some excess fabric, I press it toward the side seam.</p>
    <p><strong>Here are our pressed princess seams and cups: </strong></p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image120.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image122.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p><strong>The front half of the dress, including the cups, is prepared and I can sew bones onto it. I make a row of stay-stitches along the top edge</strong> to mark the top border of the bones.</p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image124.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image126.jpg" alt=""></p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%207_files/image128.jpg" alt=""></p>

    </div> <!-- Itemprop END: articleBody -->
